            {"type": 3, "text": "Why Hong Kong's Octopus card still beats Apple Pay for daily commute"},
            {"type": 4, "text": "A long-time MTR rider explains what the contactless wars get wrong about transit UX"},
            {"type": 1, "text": "I've ridden the MTR every workday for 14 years. In that time, Octopus has remained, against all expectations, the fastest way through a turnstile in Asia."},
            {"type": 1, "text": "Apple Pay works. Google Pay works. Both add an unmistakable half-second of latency at the gate — enough that, at peak, the queue audibly piles up behind the credit-card tap users."},
            {"type": 1, "text": "Octopus is not without flaws. Auto-reload from a bank account often fails silently. The mobile app's UI was designed in 2014 and stayed there. But the gate experience is uncontested."},
            {"type": 1, "text": "The lesson isn't 'NFC is better than contactless EMV.' It's 'closed-loop transit cards that own the gate UX win on speed, every time.'"}
          ]
        }
